Management KVM machines.

1) Install following packages:
    1.1) For Debian, Ubuntu:
        apt-get install bridge-utils arp-scan kvm ssh

2) Add user into group kvm:
    usermod kvm -G <user_name>

3) Create image file:
    kvm-img create -f qcow2 -o preallocation=metadata,cluster_size=2M,encryption=off ./ubuntu-server-10.04-64.img 500G

4) For bridge interface.
    3.1) For Debian, Ubuntu:
        3.1.1) Host file /etc/network/interfaces example:
# This file describes the network interfaces available on your system
# and how to activate them. For more information, see interfaces(5).

# The loopback network interface
auto lo
iface lo inet loopback

# The primary network interface
auto eth0
iface eth0 inet manual

auto br0
iface br0 inet static
	network 10.0.0.0
	gateway 10.0.0.1
	address 10.0.0.4
	broadcast 10.0.0.255
	netmask 255.255.255.0
	bridge_ports eth0
	bridge_maxwait 0
	bridge_stp 0
	bridge_fd 0

        3.1.2) Guest file /etc/network/interfaces example:
# This file describes the network interfaces available on your system
# and how to activate them. For more information, see interfaces(5).

# The loopback network interface
auto lo
iface lo inet loopback

# The primary network interface
auto eth0
iface eth0 inet dhcp
